Aside from that, champions like kha and rengar have huge threat ranges(like their actual flash+speedboost+leap range) that are probably far greater than anything a twitch could muster.
EDIT: And when they're fed, forget a 1 second death. Expect to die in 0.

At least you get a chance to see him *dodges Zoe missile shot from 2 miles away*

There are loads of squishy destroyers, and if you do have a fed twitch on the other team, I suggest you get a Zhonya and stay with your team.  It's like, don't walk through the jungle without Oracles by yourself with a fed Teemo on the other team... Just common sense.

